              ],
              "children": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "D7vuB",
                  "fill": "#b45309",
                  "content": "WORTH WATCHING",
                  "fontFamily": "Inter",
                  "fontSize": 11,
                  "fontWeight": "700",
                  "letterSpacing": 2
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "wMyef",
                  "fill": "#78350f",
                  "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "content": "The unfinished first probe",
                  "lineHeight": 1.25,
                  "fontFamily": "Playfair Display",
                  "fontSize": 22,
                  "fontWeight": "700"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "Y1Elkr",
                  "fill": "#78350f",
                  "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "content": "Sharon Davis is now the subject of two separate alleged ethics inquiries. The first investigation — authorized February 3 — has not yet released findings. Lovisone and Griffith voted no on a second probe specifically because of that gap. The city attorney pushed for both to proceed in parallel for due-process reasons. Whichever comes out first will reset the conversation — keep an eye on the next council agenda.",
                  "lineHeight": 1.6,
                  "fontFamily": "Newsreader",
                  "fontSize": 15,
                  "fontWeight": "normal"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "frame",
              "id": "WQemD",
              "name": "Editor's Note",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "layout": "vertical",
              "gap": 10,
              "padding": [
                8,
                0
              ],
              "children": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "vlWgC",
                  "fill": "#9ca3af",
                  "content": "FROM THE EDITOR",
                  "fontFamily": "Inter",
                  "fontSize": 11,
                  "fontWeight": "700",
                  "letterSpacing": 2
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "z2O1FB",
                  "fill": "#111827",
                  "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "content": "Two threads to pull on next time",
                  "lineHeight": 1.25,
                  "fontFamily": "Playfair Display",
                  "fontSize": 22,
                  "fontWeight": "700"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "lnD1J",
                  "fill": "#374151",
                  "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "content": "The most interesting line of the night came from Griffith: staff's slide deck for composting Option 1 and Option 4 was missing a $5–7/month savings figure that residents would actually see from the EPR refund alone, with no other change. That's the kind of detail that decides whether a “stay the course” option is good politics or just inertia. The other thing to watch: Moorman's pitch on Option 2 wasn't just policy preference — it depends on Republic's representation that the EPR refund will be large enough to fully offset curbside organics costs. If the negotiated reimbursement comes in lower than today's estimate, that math changes.",
                  "lineHeight": 1.65,
                  "fontFamily": "Newsreader",
                  "fontSize": 15,
                  "fontWeight": "normal"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "azSYl",
                  "fill": "#9ca3af",
                  "content": "— RW",
                  "fontFamily": "Newsreader",
                  "fontSize": 14,
                  "fontWeight": "normal",
                  "fontStyle": "italic"
                }
              ]
            },
